UML:TaggedValue.value: used to describe any door inside a building including entrance of this building
record the floors accessible by vertical pathway. the value could be 1;2;3;4 or 1-4

Logical unit consisted of several floors in a building according to the function, ownership, such as commercial floors, office floors and accommodation floors in a building complex---corresponding to BuildingSubdivision of CityGML 3.0
Feature could be any space or unit, opened or closed or half-closed, for example, a room, a parking site at the parking floor,an information desk in an airport.
record the order of the floor which an unit space is on
the number of individula buildings which are composed of a complex building
Using floor instead of storey is to follow with OSM
Basic description of a floor including its main usages and other information

the order of floor used in OSM, which can be like 2.5 to show the space between the 2nd floor and the 3rd floor.The half floor will not be counted in overGroundFloorCount and underGroundFloorCount of Building class. In some buildings, only a name instead of a numerical order to show the level of floor, so the type is string.

BuildingSections can describe the linking parts between buildings of a building complex. Moreover, a building can also be decomposed in (vertical) parts, where each part defines a building section (from IfcBuilding of IFC)
area with specific usages or ownershops, same as BuildingUnit of CityGML BuildingModel on a single floor, for example, different departments in a same floor
